1
00:00:07,941 --> 00:00:09,142
[explosion]

2
00:00:09,209 --> 00:00:10,343
‐ What was that?

3
00:00:10,410 --> 00:00:11,712
‐ I think a plasma grenade.

4
00:00:11,778 --> 00:00:14,447
David: Focus, guys.
Pitohui's the mission.

5
00:00:14,515 --> 00:00:16,750
‐ [gunshot]
‐ Open fire on the wall!

6
00:00:16,817 --> 00:00:18,719
‐ [yelling]

7
00:00:18,785 --> 00:00:19,786
[shotgun blasts]

8
00:00:19,853 --> 00:00:22,288
‐ [groans]
‐ Lax!

9
00:00:23,189 --> 00:00:24,424
[explosion]

10
00:00:27,093 --> 00:00:29,029
[photon sword hums]

11
00:00:44,177 --> 00:00:49,215
‐ Now this is fun.

12
00:00:51,417 --> 00:00:52,418
[yells]

13
00:00:52,485 --> 00:00:53,419
[laughs]

14
00:00:54,521 --> 00:00:55,756
‐ [yelling]

15
00:00:57,457 --> 00:00:59,092
‐ [grunts]

16
00:00:59,159 --> 00:01:01,394
‐ I'm not going down that easy!

17
00:01:03,096 --> 00:01:05,298
‐ [laughs]

18
00:01:06,399 --> 00:01:10,136
It's time to die, boys!

19
00:01:12,438 --> 00:01:14,741
You don't know
when to quit, do you!

20
00:01:14,808 --> 00:01:18,645
‐ What? Did you think
I'd be scared of a glow stick?

21
00:01:18,712 --> 00:01:22,215
‐ That's right. This kind
of thing doesn't interest you.

22
00:01:22,282 --> 00:01:23,984
Guns are your jam.

23
00:01:24,050 --> 00:01:26,252
‐ Yeah. So what?

24
00:01:26,319 --> 00:01:28,088
‐ Bet you didn't know.

25
00:01:28,154 --> 00:01:31,792
This Muramasa F9,
it's got a neat feature.

26
00:01:31,858 --> 00:01:33,760
‐ [grunting]

27
00:01:41,635 --> 00:01:43,970
‐ [laughs]

28
00:01:44,037 --> 00:01:47,073
‐ Is‐‐Is this fun for you?!

29
00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:48,842
You crazy bitch!

30
00:01:48,909 --> 00:01:51,244
‐ I'm loving every second
of it, actually.

31
00:01:51,311 --> 00:01:54,715
And now I'll enjoy
your death, too...

32
00:01:54,781 --> 00:01:56,216
bitch.

33
00:01:57,483 --> 00:01:59,653
‐ Pitohui!

34
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:00,654
[yells]

35
00:02:00,721 --> 00:02:02,556
‐ Yes!

36
00:02:02,623 --> 00:02:04,725
You know it!

37
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:07,728
That is me!

38
00:02:07,794 --> 00:02:09,730
‐ [gags]

39
00:02:09,796 --> 00:02:11,732
[both screaming]

40
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:13,700
‐ Thanks for playing!

41
00:02:17,771 --> 00:02:19,339
[laughs]

42
00:02:21,642 --> 00:02:23,577
[laughing]

43
00:02:30,350 --> 00:02:32,485
[laughter continues]

44
00:02:37,123 --> 00:02:39,125
Fuka: <i>Hello! Earth to LLENN.</i>

45
00:02:39,192 --> 00:02:40,861
Boss: <i>What happened in there?</i>

46
00:02:40,927 --> 00:02:42,128
[brush rustling]

47
00:02:42,195 --> 00:02:45,599
LLENN: Th‐The whole team's dead.

48
00:02:45,666 --> 00:02:48,702
Pito killed
every last one of 'em.

49
00:02:48,769 --> 00:02:49,703
Fuka: <i>Whoa.</i>

50
00:02:49,770 --> 00:02:51,171
Boss: <i>No way.</i>

51
00:02:51,237 --> 00:02:52,939
‐ H‐How is someone like me

52
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:55,809
supposed to beat
someone like that?

53
00:02:55,876 --> 00:02:57,811
["Ryusei" by Eir Aoi playing]

54
00:03:10,123 --> 00:03:12,258
‐ [singing in Japanese]

55
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:45,325
<i>♪ ...safety ♪</i>

56
00:03:45,391 --> 00:03:47,327
[singing in Japanese]

57
00:04:13,987 --> 00:04:16,456
<i>♪ The darkest night ♪</i>

58
00:04:16,523 --> 00:04:18,659
[singing in Japanese]

59
00:04:20,561 --> 00:04:24,731
<i>♪ The darkest night ♪</i>

60
00:04:30,737 --> 00:04:31,672
‐ [gasps]

61
00:04:35,742 --> 00:04:38,478
[whimpers]

62
00:04:38,545 --> 00:04:41,281
[Terminal buzzing]

63
00:04:44,518 --> 00:04:45,652
[buzzing stops]

64
00:04:49,923 --> 00:04:52,492
Spectator: This'll be
the last scan of the tourney.

65
00:04:52,559 --> 00:04:55,428
‐ Mm. There's only
four teams left.

66
00:04:55,495 --> 00:04:58,599
‐ Crap.
PM4's got this in the bag.

67
00:04:58,665 --> 00:05:01,267
‐ LLENN can still
pull through, man!

68
00:05:01,334 --> 00:05:03,604
‐ T‐S is still
up on the rampart.

69
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:05,672
What are they waiting for?

70
00:05:05,739 --> 00:05:09,342
‐ I bet they'll run out the game
up there, sniping at everyone.

71
00:05:09,409 --> 00:05:10,343
‐ [groans]

72
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:11,912
God, they make me sick.

73
00:05:11,978 --> 00:05:14,681
If they were real men,
they'd fight toe‐to‐toe.

74
00:05:14,748 --> 00:05:17,518
Except for M, everyone
out there's a friggin' wimp.

75
00:05:19,085 --> 00:05:21,487
Hang in there, ladies.

76
00:05:23,089 --> 00:05:24,925
‐ How am I gonna do this?

77
00:05:26,392 --> 00:05:29,195
What do I do?
What do I do? What do I do?

78
00:05:29,262 --> 00:05:31,898
Oh, come on. Think.
You need a plan.

79
00:05:31,965 --> 00:05:34,601
A plan, a plan,
but what kind of plan?

80
00:05:34,668 --> 00:05:37,270
Boss: <i>New plan, everyone!</i>
<i>Let's storm the cabin!</i>

81
00:05:37,337 --> 00:05:38,271
‐ Huh?

82
00:05:38,338 --> 00:05:39,906
Wh‐Wh‐What?!

83
00:05:39,973 --> 00:05:41,141
[automatic gunfire]

84
00:05:41,207 --> 00:05:43,944
Wait! Don't go without me!
I'm not ready yet!

85
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:46,412
Boss: <i>Sorry.</i>
<i>You're taking too long.</i>

86
00:05:46,479 --> 00:05:48,682
<i>I'm calling the shots now.</i>

87
00:05:50,216 --> 00:05:51,518
‐ What's up?

88
00:05:51,585 --> 00:05:54,254
‐ B‐Boss and her team
are just charging right in!

89
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:55,321
‐ Nice.

90
00:05:55,388 --> 00:05:56,757
‐ No, it's suicide.

91
00:05:56,823 --> 00:05:59,025
I can't kill Pito without them.

92
00:05:59,092 --> 00:06:01,828
We need a plan,
but I can't think of any.

93
00:06:01,895 --> 00:06:03,363
‐ Right.
I'm charging in with 'em.

94
00:06:03,429 --> 00:06:04,430
‐ Huh?!

95
00:06:04,497 --> 00:06:06,432
‐ That's as good a plan as any.

96
00:06:06,499 --> 00:06:08,201
Just you watch.
We'll catch Pito,

97
00:06:08,268 --> 00:06:09,503
wrap her up in a mat,

98
00:06:09,570 --> 00:06:12,138
and bring her right back here
in nothing flat.

99
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:13,540
‐ [giggling]
‐ No, stop.

100
00:06:13,607 --> 00:06:15,175
Would you wait a second?!

101
00:06:15,241 --> 00:06:16,810
Get back here!

102
00:06:16,877 --> 00:06:17,978
Whoa!

103
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:20,413
You gotta be kidding.

104
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:22,583
Of all the stupid‐‐Come on!

105
00:06:22,649 --> 00:06:25,552
Fuka: <i>Calm down,</i>
<i>and take your time.</i>

106
00:06:25,619 --> 00:06:27,721
<i>You'll get loose eventually.</i>

107
00:06:27,788 --> 00:06:31,324
‐ Fuka! Didn't you
hear anything I said?!

108
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:33,527
You can't charge in
all by yourself!

109
00:06:33,594 --> 00:06:36,296
<i>‐ Whoever undoes</i>
<i>that Gordian knot</i>

110
00:06:36,362 --> 00:06:38,865
<i>is destined to rule the world.</i>

111
00:06:38,932 --> 00:06:41,602
[laughs]

112
00:06:41,668 --> 00:06:44,437
‐ [groans] Dang it!

113
00:06:44,505 --> 00:06:46,406
[groans]

114
00:06:46,472 --> 00:06:49,576
‐ Ladies, hit 'em hard and fast!

115
00:06:49,643 --> 00:06:51,578
Team: Roger that!

116
00:06:54,548 --> 00:06:57,618
M: We got four Amazons
heading straight for us.

117
00:06:59,853 --> 00:07:01,321
They're getting closer.

118
00:07:01,387 --> 00:07:03,223
Four hundred meters now.

119
00:07:03,289 --> 00:07:05,091
Standing by for orders.

120
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:10,130
‐ Well, well, looky here.

121
00:07:10,196 --> 00:07:13,333
I see LLENN's friend coming.

122
00:07:13,399 --> 00:07:16,603
She's, uh,
skipping across the field.

123
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:19,906
The weird thing is
I don't see LLENN anywhere.

124
00:07:19,973 --> 00:07:22,643
Do you have
any idea why that is?

125
00:07:22,709 --> 00:07:24,845
M: <i>No, I don't. From here,</i>

126
00:07:24,911 --> 00:07:27,447
<i>it looks like they're</i>
<i>attacking out of desperation,</i>

127
00:07:27,514 --> 00:07:29,449
<i>like they're</i>
<i>begging to be shot.</i>

128
00:07:29,516 --> 00:07:32,452
‐ Seems awfully fishy.

129
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:34,855
I know they're up to something.

130
00:07:34,921 --> 00:07:37,257
‐ Well, until we
find out what that is,

131
00:07:37,323 --> 00:07:39,292
thinning their ranks
is an option.

132
00:07:39,359 --> 00:07:41,261
‐ <i>I guess that's all we can do.</i>

133
00:07:41,327 --> 00:07:42,996
<i>Here are your orders, then.</i>

134
00:07:43,063 --> 00:07:46,867
Kill them
with extreme prejudice.

135
00:07:48,168 --> 00:07:49,703
‐ [yelps]

136
00:07:49,770 --> 00:07:51,237
‐ [gasps]
‐ [laughs]

137
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:54,641
<i>A bullet bounced off my helmet.</i>
<i>Talk about lucky.</i>

138
00:07:54,708 --> 00:07:56,309
‐ Fuka, stay down!

139
00:07:56,376 --> 00:07:59,479
‐ [giggles] Nah, I'm good.

140
00:08:03,416 --> 00:08:06,520
‐ It's really not fair
when they're so short.

141
00:08:07,453 --> 00:08:10,557
Well? How are you doing?

142
00:08:10,624 --> 00:08:13,126
‐ I got one so far.

143
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:18,164
‐ Ohh!
‐ Nice shot!

144
00:08:18,231 --> 00:08:19,700
‐ He just got another!

145
00:08:19,766 --> 00:08:22,002
‐ Whoa!
‐ [overlapping chatter]

146
00:08:22,068 --> 00:08:23,770
‐ Oh, come on.

147
00:08:24,671 --> 00:08:25,939
Sophie: What's up?

148
00:08:26,006 --> 00:08:28,942
‐ Boss and the others
are on that suicide run.

149
00:08:29,009 --> 00:08:30,711
‐ [sighs]

150
00:08:43,489 --> 00:08:44,691
[single shot]

151
00:08:49,563 --> 00:08:52,098
‐ Why's she smiling?

152
00:08:52,165 --> 00:08:54,067
Aha.

153
00:08:57,170 --> 00:08:59,840
‐ [panting]

154
00:08:59,906 --> 00:09:00,841
Oh, great.

155
00:09:00,907 --> 00:09:03,910
Looks like I'm
the last one of us left.

156
00:09:09,482 --> 00:09:11,084
Gotta hand it to M.

157
00:09:11,151 --> 00:09:14,955
If there's anyone sharp enough
to figure us out, it's him.

158
00:09:29,369 --> 00:09:30,904
[crowd groaning]

159
00:09:30,971 --> 00:09:33,106
Sophie: That's a shame.

160
00:09:33,173 --> 00:09:36,309
Her timing
was way off at the end.

161
00:09:36,376 --> 00:09:40,013
‐ I dare you to tell her that
when she gets here.

162
00:09:42,115 --> 00:09:43,850
‐ Come on!

163
00:09:43,917 --> 00:09:46,286
Fuka: <i>Don't tell me</i>
<i>Alexander the Great's</i>

164
00:09:46,352 --> 00:09:47,888
<i>still working on that knot.</i>

165
00:09:47,954 --> 00:09:50,757
<i>Remember the prophecy.</i>
<i>It specifically states</i>

166
00:09:50,824 --> 00:09:54,427
<i>that you cannot rule the world</i>
<i>unless you untie it.</i>

167
00:09:54,494 --> 00:09:55,629
‐ Yeah, I know!

168
00:09:57,130 --> 00:09:59,165
[sighs] Stupid knot.

169
00:09:59,232 --> 00:10:00,466
This'll do you.

170
00:10:00,534 --> 00:10:02,969
‐ [Fuka screams]
‐ [gasps] Fuka?

171
00:10:03,036 --> 00:10:05,138
‐ [Fuka screams]
‐ Fuka!

172
00:10:05,205 --> 00:10:06,139
Fuka!

173
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:09,943
I took care of SHINC.
How are you doing?

174
00:10:10,010 --> 00:10:13,279
‐ Eh, not good. Frustrated.

175
00:10:13,346 --> 00:10:14,981
LLENN's not coming out.

176
00:10:15,048 --> 00:10:18,384
I shot up her partner
and everything.

177
00:10:21,387 --> 00:10:24,157
I can't believe
she's not coming to her rescue.

178
00:10:24,224 --> 00:10:26,326
‐ God, would you
just finish her already?

179
00:10:26,392 --> 00:10:28,394
[Pito chuckles] What's that?

180
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:31,131
Kindness? Mercy? Compassion?

181
00:10:31,197 --> 00:10:34,367
M: Mercy and compassion
are the same thing,

182
00:10:34,434 --> 00:10:36,503
and, no, it's not about that.

183
00:10:36,570 --> 00:10:39,740
LLENN isn't coming to save her,
because she doesn't have to.

184
00:10:39,806 --> 00:10:41,942
This isn't a real battle.

185
00:10:42,008 --> 00:10:44,144
And while you mess around
with her friend there,

186
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:45,979
LLENN's figuring out
our blind spot,

187
00:10:46,046 --> 00:10:48,949
and the last surviving team's
closing in.

188
00:10:49,015 --> 00:10:52,986
I want to X her out ASAP so we
can be ready for everyone else.

189
00:10:53,053 --> 00:10:55,255
Pito: Can't we just wait
a little longer?

190
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:57,223
‐ Fine. I'll kill her.

191
00:10:57,290 --> 00:10:58,692
‐ [sighs]

192
00:10:58,759 --> 00:11:00,326
Okay, jeez.

193
00:11:03,063 --> 00:11:04,598
Oopsie.

194
00:11:04,665 --> 00:11:06,166
Only got her hand.

195
00:11:06,232 --> 00:11:08,368
Still getting
used to this rifle.

196
00:11:14,474 --> 00:11:15,909
Damn, she's tough!

197
00:11:15,976 --> 00:11:18,178
LLENN sure knows
how to pick a teammate.

198
00:11:18,244 --> 00:11:19,412
[laughs]

199
00:11:19,479 --> 00:11:21,081
She's not a threat anymore,

200
00:11:21,147 --> 00:11:23,817
at least
for the next two minutes.

201
00:11:23,884 --> 00:11:28,188
‐ Um, Hey, LLENN,
I got bad news for you.

202
00:11:28,254 --> 00:11:30,824
It was an honor
serving on your team,

203
00:11:30,891 --> 00:11:34,027
<i>but my hands and feet are gone,</i>
<i>and I'm stuck.</i>

204
00:11:34,094 --> 00:11:36,329
‐ That's 'cause you
charged in by yourself!

205
00:11:36,396 --> 00:11:39,232
<i>‐ Yeah, but I don't regret it</i>
<i>or anything. That's for sure.</i>

206
00:11:39,299 --> 00:11:40,634
‐ You should!

207
00:11:40,701 --> 00:11:43,369
<i>‐</i> Hey, it's better
<i>than sitting around like you,</i>

208
00:11:43,436 --> 00:11:45,105
<i>all nervous and indecisive.</i>

209
00:11:45,171 --> 00:11:47,674
<i>I did what I could,</i>
<i>and I'm good with that.</i>

210
00:11:47,741 --> 00:11:49,510
<i>I bet if you asked</i>
<i>Boss and the others,</i>

211
00:11:49,576 --> 00:11:51,578
<i>they'd say the same thing, too.</i>

212
00:11:51,645 --> 00:11:53,446
‐ [groaning]

213
00:11:53,514 --> 00:11:54,981
[screams]

214
00:11:55,048 --> 00:11:56,817
If I killed Pito at the start,

215
00:11:56,883 --> 00:11:58,251
none of this
would have happened!

216
00:11:58,318 --> 00:12:02,055
But they dropped us
so far away from each other,

217
00:12:02,122 --> 00:12:05,526
and then people got in the way,
and my ammo supply went down.

218
00:12:05,592 --> 00:12:07,828
And then,
when I finally get to her,

219
00:12:07,894 --> 00:12:10,363
she's turned into
a rampaging monster.

220
00:12:10,430 --> 00:12:14,000
I wanted to take a minute and
figure out a plan of attack,

221
00:12:14,067 --> 00:12:16,202
but everyone just ran in
and got killed.

222
00:12:19,773 --> 00:12:22,042
Instead of doing something,

223
00:12:22,108 --> 00:12:26,346
I'm still
standing here, shaking.

224
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:28,515
Aah! I've had it!

225
00:12:28,582 --> 00:12:30,717
I'm done worrying about Pito!

226
00:12:30,784 --> 00:12:33,253
She can win this thing
for all I care!

227
00:12:33,319 --> 00:12:35,656
She's so strong,
she probably will.

228
00:12:35,722 --> 00:12:39,092
Why should I stress over someone
killing her before I do?!

229
00:12:39,159 --> 00:12:40,994
That's her problem, not mine!

230
00:12:41,061 --> 00:12:43,463
And if she kills me first,
that's fine, too.

231
00:12:43,530 --> 00:12:44,865
If I die, I die!

232
00:12:44,931 --> 00:12:47,500
Fuka: <i>So what are you gonna do?</i>

233
00:12:47,568 --> 00:12:48,902
‐ I'm gonna kill!

234
00:12:48,969 --> 00:12:50,704
‐ Kill who?
‐ Pito!

235
00:12:50,771 --> 00:12:51,838
‐ <i>Okay. How?</i>

236
00:12:51,905 --> 00:12:53,106
‐ I don't know!

237
00:12:53,173 --> 00:12:55,509
I'll use my gun
if I have bullets left

238
00:12:55,576 --> 00:12:58,444
or my knife. I don't care
what I use to do it.

239
00:12:58,512 --> 00:13:00,446
I'm gonna kill Pito and win!

240
00:13:00,514 --> 00:13:02,315
P‐chan: Awesome!

241
00:13:02,382 --> 00:13:03,483
[LLENN gasps]

242
00:13:03,550 --> 00:13:05,719
‐ I'm with you all the way.

243
00:13:05,786 --> 00:13:07,521
Let's do this.

244
00:13:07,588 --> 00:13:10,323
‐ Sweet. It's you and me, then.

245
00:13:10,390 --> 00:13:13,694
LLENN: <i>We're gonna</i>
<i>murder Pito together!</i>

246
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:16,129
‐ You go, girl. Get her.

247
00:13:16,196 --> 00:13:18,732
Tanya: Just like in SJ 1.

248
00:13:18,799 --> 00:13:21,001
Toma: An erratic LLENN
is the best LLENN.

249
00:13:21,067 --> 00:13:23,303
‐ Go, you little psycho. Go.

250
00:13:23,369 --> 00:13:26,507
‐ Damn it. This is
what I wanted all along.

251
00:13:26,573 --> 00:13:31,344
This is the go‐for‐broke version
of LLENN I wanted to fight.

252
00:13:41,822 --> 00:13:44,825
Pito: Look! There she is!

253
00:13:44,891 --> 00:13:47,728
M: Yup. I see her, too.

254
00:13:47,794 --> 00:13:49,796
‐ Don't forget. She's mine.

255
00:13:49,863 --> 00:13:52,733
If you kill her, I'll kill you.

256
00:13:52,799 --> 00:13:53,800
Wait.

257
00:13:53,867 --> 00:13:55,769
She's running away?!

258
00:13:55,836 --> 00:13:57,604
What the hell?! Of all the‐‐

259
00:13:57,671 --> 00:13:59,673
Unh! Get back here!

260
00:13:59,740 --> 00:14:01,407
Come on! We're going after her!

261
00:14:01,474 --> 00:14:03,710
‐ What'll we do
about her partner?

262
00:14:03,777 --> 00:14:05,011
‐ We can kill her later.

263
00:14:05,078 --> 00:14:07,548
‐ You sure? She might be
fully healed by then.

264
00:14:07,614 --> 00:14:08,949
‐ Who cares?!

265
00:14:09,015 --> 00:14:10,851
‐ [blow lands]
